%S A394697 9,56,600,14940,576856,42752576,5666291496,1377165318000,
%T A394697 602917863487951,491349880347810732,717837429519886358358,
%U A394697 1906549046833287409861952,9139679913945121323495407100,79450391756097313369708715135488,1239633081570241324597609845836883982,35261313543116561639195408117355324062850
%N A394697 a(n) = max_k [x^k] I(G, x), where G is the n X n toroidal king graph and I(G,x) is its independence polynomial.
%C A394697 The maximum coefficient measures the modal (most common) independent-set size: how many independent sets achieve the most-common cardinality.
%C A394697 a(n) is empirically log-concave for n <= 21.
%C A394697 Empirical: log(a(n))/n^2 increases monotonically from 0.244 at n=3 to 0.290 at n=21, suggesting a finite per-vertex peak entropy in the range 0.29-0.30 for 2D king packings.
%C A394697 Conjecture: a(n)^(1/n^2) tends to A247413. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 06 2026
%H A394697 Todd Hildebrant, <a href="/A394697/b394697.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 3..21</a>
%H A394697 Todd Hildebrant, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.14416">Transfer Operators and Independence Polynomials for Strong Powers of Circulant Graphs</a>, arXiv:2604.14416 [math.CO], 2026.
%F A394697 a(n) = max_k [x^k] tr(T_n(x)^n), where T_n(x) is the |IS(C_n)|-dimensional transfer matrix with T(A,B) = x^|A| if A,B are independent sets in C_n with A intersect N[B] = {}, and 0 otherwise; |IS(C_n)| = L_n (Lucas).
%e A394697 For n=3, I(K_9, x) = 1 + 9*x; max coef a(3) = 9 at k=1 (the n=3 toroidal king graph is K_9).
%e A394697 For n=4, I(G,x) = 1 + 16*x + 56*x^2 + 48*x^3 + 12*x^4; a(4) = 56 at k=2.
%e A394697 For n=5, I(G,x) = 1 + 25*x + 200*x^2 + 600*x^3 + 575*x^4 + 10*x^5; a(5) = 600 at k=3.
%Y A394697 Cf. A189889 (independence number alpha(C_n^2)), A067958 (total IS count I(C_n^2,1)).
%Y A394697 Cf. A247413.
